  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 0f3a2c8c7b8f4d9c9d5a3d11d5f50101, type: 3}
  m_Name: PokedexRobin
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  entryId: bird_robin
  commonName: American Robin
  scientificName: Turdus migratorius
  icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 9997adc999aa5a6438387a05699f5ba8, type: 3}
  category: Bird
  habitat: Open Woodlands & Parks
  height: 23 - 28 cm
  weight: 75 - 85 g
  diet: Omnivore
  rarity: Very common
  shortDescription: A large, prominent songbird famous for its warm, reddish-orange
    breast and cheerful morning songs.
  behaviorNotes: Frequently hops across the ground searching for food. Flies up into
    mid-level branches when disturbed.
  observationTips: Often found directly on the forest floor, tilting its head to
    look and listen for earthworms moving in the soil.
  funFact: Despite its name, it is not closely related to the European Robin; it
    is actually a true thrush and is one of America's most widespread birds.
  facts:
  - Their mud-lined nests are meticulously crafted, with females pulling grass and
    mud together using their beak and breast.
  - Robin eggs are famous for their unique, vibrant bright-blue color, a shade caused
    by a pigment in the female's bile.
  - They are known as a foundational herald of spring, often migrating back north
    just as the ground begins to thaw.
